    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Generic term used for several types of cuirasses worn by Roman soldiers, made of leather, bronze, or iron plates or scales, or of mail.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
